        <slide environment="" chapter_type="Week" wbtag="slide" id="s3" slide="3" course="Math 2070" chapter="13" section="" subsection="" subsubsection="" chapter_title="" section_title=""><keywords slide="3" environ="slide" chapter="13" course="Math 2070"><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Groups</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Definition</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Examples</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Subgroups</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Cosets</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Lagrange's Theorem</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Generators</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Cyclic groups</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Group homomorphism</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Kernel</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Isomorphism</keyword><keyword chapter="13" slide="3">Example</keyword></keywords>
<xh:h3 xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="">Groups</xh:h3>
<xh:hr xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment=""/>
<col_ol environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_ol">
<col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Definition</xh:b>
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Examples</xh:b>
<newcol environment="newcol" chapter_type="" wbtag="newcol">
\[
S_n, A_n, D_n, \GL(n), \SL(n), \mathbb{Z}_n
\]
</newcol>
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
\[
g^n = e_G \Leftrightarrow \ord g | n
\]
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Subgroups</xh:b>, <xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Cosets</xh:b>
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Lagrange's Theorem</xh:b>
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
\[
\ord g\;|\;\abs{G}
\]
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Generators</xh:b>
\[
D_n = \langle r, s\rangle,\quad srs = r^{-1}
\]
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Cyclic groups</xh:b>
\[
\abs{\langle g \rangle} = \ord g \text{ if } \ord g &lt; \infty.
\]
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
A group of prime order is necessarily cyclic.
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Group homomorphism</xh:b>, <xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Kernel</xh:b>, <xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Isomorphism</xh:b>
<xh:br xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol"/>
<xh:b xmlns:xh="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" environment="col_ol">Example</xh:b>
<newcol environment="newcol" chapter_type="" wbtag="newcol">
Fix $h \in G$.
\[
\phi_h : G \longrightarrow G
\]
\[
\phi_h(g) = h^{-1}gh, \quad g \in G.
\]
</newcol>
</col_li><col_li environment="col_ol" chapter_type="" wbtag="col_li">
Any cyclic group is isomorphic to either $\mathbb{Z}_n$ or $\mathbb{Z}$.
</col_li></col_ol>
